5: We've got the whole day off today!
15:
So let's make the most of it and
have some fun!
25: Hehe, you two sure are fired up.
31:
Why wouldn't I be? It's been a while
since we got to hang out together,
Suzuka!
41:
Now that you mention it... It feels like
all we've done lately is train.
46: We do have a big race coming up.
50:
But it's also important to take
breaks, you know?
55:
Hehe, that's true. Let's forget
everything else and just enjoy
ourselves for today.
65:
Do you have shops you
recommend? Oh, I'm so curious to
see what you're into!
73:
Th-that's really red... Almost as red
as the stuff El eats!
82:
Yes. It's a blood-red pancake
topped with liquid acid and a
tapioca meteor.
85:
You can earn prize money if you
finish a whole plate.
91:
Hnngh... I can handle volume, but
not spice! If only El were here...
96:
Um, Stella... Spe and I aren't very
good with spicy food.
101:
Oh... What about having the Tapioca
Meteor tea instead?
105:
I recommend the Heaven topping.
It's very sweet and gooey.
113: Silence Suzuka! I finally found you!
115:
I can't believe you ran away after
becoming my master's rival!
124:
So you're students of the teacher
who made one of the golems that
raced against us...
127:
Yep, the one who asked for your
data the other day. Thanks for that,
by the way! It was top quality stuff!
129:
Are you crazy? That data only
showed how absurd it was for a
two-legged living being to output
that much speed!
131:
Rgh... Your motor functions are
phenomenal... Ideal even! Us golem
researchers can only dream of such
numbers...
134:
You must like Suzuka a lot to study
her that much.
137:
Th-that's not... My master might be a
fan of yours, but I'm not!
139:
I'm going to make a golem that
surpasses you!
142:
Should I take that to mean you're
challenging me to a race?
145:
Not right away, of course. I realize
we both have preparations to make
first.
147:
But if you're too busy to accept, I
won't complain. A competition
doesn't mean anything unless all
contestants are in top shape!
154:
I'm curious to see what you have in
store.
159:
Wow, it's amazing that you can get
something like that to move!
162:
Special Week, I have a question for
you.
164: What do you think of Silence Suzuka?
167:
Do you mean while she's running a
race?
171:
...Everyone's always chasing after
her from behind, keeping their eyes
on her back.
174:
Sometimes, I'm scared she might
run so far into the horizon that she'll
disappear...
177:
But I won't let that fear or anything
else stop me. I'll catch up to her, no
matter what.
182:
I thought it would be annoying if I
was the only one obsessed with
beating her, but if there are others,
then I'm not adding anything new to
her plate!
185:
Hehe, I wouldn't worry about that! I
think Suzuka's happy to accept your
challenge!
193:
Silence Suzuka. I'll show you what
golems are really capable of.
196:
...You can try, but I won't let anyone
take the lead from me.
201:
Its artificial feet are heavy... I can
keenly feel the pressure...
205:
The intensity is there, even if it isn't a
living being.
221: I can go faster... Much, much faster!
231:
Its footsteps were heavy, unlike the
racers I'm used to...
234:
But I still felt the pressure to win... So,
um...
238: It was a lot of fun to race against.
241:
That's... not really helpful information
for your research, is it? I'm sorry...
246:
So you better keep on winning until
our next race! Or else!
253:
There's still new views I want to see...
I know I haven't reached my full
potential yet.
256: Ngh... I-I'll be cheering you on, then!
263:
I'll keep reaching faster and faster
speeds. Just watch!
